#length of the trail in miles for each county

#counties that intersect
trail_segments = gpd.overlay(ice_age_trail, counties[counties['intersects_trail']], how='intersection')

#calculate distance of intersecting segments
trail_segments['segment_length_m'] = trail_segments.length
trail_segments['segment_length_miles'] = trail_segments['segment_length_m'] * 0.000621371

#group by county
trail_by_county = trail_segments.groupby('NAME').agg({'segment_length_miles': 'sum'}).reset_index()

#descending order
trail_by_county_sorted = trail_by_county.sort_values(by='segment_length_miles', ascending=False)

print(trail_by_county_sorted)

#Spatial join function
## point in polygon function
def count_points(polydf, pointdf, predicate='intersects'):

    polydf.drop(['point_count'], axis=1, errors="ignore", inplace=True)

    polydf['ix'] = polydf.index

    poly_join = gpd.sjoin(polydf, pointdf, how='inner', predicate=predicate)

    # create new column and fill it with 1's
    poly_join['point_count'] = 1

    # groupby BoroCode, aggregate based on count column
    tmp_df = poly_join.groupby('ix').agg({'point_count':'sum'})

    # merge dataframes together, subset into only fields of interest
    merged_df = polydf.merge(tmp_df, on='ix')[['point_count', 'ix']]

    # merge to the original
    polydf_new = polydf.merge(merged_df, on='ix', how='left')

    # replace NaNs with 0s
    polydf_new['point_count'] = polydf_new['point_count'].fillna(0)

    return(polydf_new['point_count'])
